      "id": "5a93c517_d4ec1992",
      "file_path": "blueprints/k8s-inventory.yaml-template",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 88,
      "message": "There is some plugin/k8s/DNS magic.  When a component exposes one or more ports, the plugin creates a k8s Service, which in turn causes an entry to created in the k8s DNS.   All containers are configured automatically to use the k8s DNS and to have a search path that lets it resolve services in its k8s namespace.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-26 14:48:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_54a9e979",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_54a6c954",
      "file_path": "blueprints/k8s-inventory.yaml-template",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 88,
      "message": "> the plugin creates a k8s Service, which in turn causes an entry to created in the k8s DNS\n\nIs the name that is used to register with k8s DNS the properties \"name\" value in the blueprint?",
